Description: WebSocket server in Rust for real-time messaging
 This project implements a WebSocket server in Rust for
 real-time messaging, notifications, and mailbox management.
 It is designed as a service for the Document Management
 System of the National Protection Unit (UNP).
 .
 Runtime dependencies:
  - adduser: creates the ws-unp system user on install.
  - postgresql-client: needed to apply the bundled SQL schema
    (db/ws.sql) with psql when using --migrate.
  - openssl: CLI tool for generating and inspecting TLS
    certificates used in WSS mode.

